Five suspects stormed into the NWJ shop on Monday afternoon, and made off with items from the display shelves. JOHANNESBURG Police are searching for five men after a jewellery shop was robbed at Forest Hill Mall in Centurion.The men stormed into the NWJ shop on Monday afternoon, and made off with items from the display shelves. They managed to run away from the scene.The police s captain Bongikosi Msimanga has called on anyone with information to come forward. No arrests at this stage, no shots were fired and no injuries [have been reported]. We are still investigating a case of business robbery, and we appeal to the community to assist with any information regarding the incident. 